<item>
            <title>[WFLY-4511] CMTTxInterceptor.invokeInOurTx contains stale code handling ApplicationDeadlockException</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-4511</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Description of problem:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;git://git.app.eng.bos.redhat.com/jbossas/jboss-as.git&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ejb3/src/main/java/org/jboss/as/ejb3/tx/CMTTxInterceptor.java&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;There is stale code catching ApplicationDeadlockException and attempting to retry the transaction. This results in a failure if the exception is raised and retry does not occur.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;How reproducible:&lt;br/&gt;
Consistently&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps to Reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Visual Inspection&lt;br/&gt;
OR&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Register a transaction Synchronization object which raises the exception during beforeCompletion()&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Note that EAP no longer raises this exception. The catch block code handling ApplicationDeadlockException seems to be an artifact of EAP 4 and should simply be removed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Actual results:&lt;br/&gt;
Retry does not occur&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected results:&lt;br/&gt;
Retry should not be attempted by this code&lt;/p&gt;</description>
